{{hstr|5401}}
*נשׁק / nâshaq / naw-shak'
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root (identical with {{HH|5400}}, through the idea of fastening up; compare {{HH|2388}} and {{HH|2836}}); 
=== Verb ===
to [[kiss]], literally or figuratively (touch); also (as a mode of attachment), to equip with weapons: - armed (men), rule, kiss, that touched.